ass=title> Re: Should verant finally fix the old EQ?</span><hr size=1> eq's game play needs to be revised 100%.  <br>
<br>
its sad to see a game w/ so much potential be hindered by the massive amounts of time needed to proceed in the game (no fungi/twinking.)  exp is just so shamefully @#%$. <p><imgsrc=:http://www.homestead.com/Maijun></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 5:31:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mines.edu/students/g/gbassett/orion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should verant finally fix the old EQ?</span><hr size=1> Well, people can go from 1 to 60 in under a week.  And some people take 100+ days just to hit 55 (like me).  It depends how you play the game.  The great thing about EQ is that it's so expansive that you CAN play it so many different ways.  There are powergamers, questers, roleplayers, explorers, Raiders, Exp'rs, traders, crafters, and more.  As for the zone lines being 'broken'.  Zonelines that go no-where is Verant leaving themselves the ability to add more old world zones on.  (Something for the people who don't buy expansions.)  True there are old world quests that need fixing, but I believe that is a focus after Velious. <p>--------------------------
