</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upedriccuf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pedric Cuf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 7:18:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should verant finally fix the old EQ?</span><hr size=1> I've been kind of worrying how well I'll be able to run EQ after I install Luclin. I don't have good enough hardware to support the new graphic engine, and frankly from what I've seen I don't really mind. I just want to be able to play the same game with new zones and characters. I really hope I'll be able to without having to go out and spend a lot of money and have five minute zone times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utoklan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toklan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 7:38:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should verant finally fix the old EQ?</span><hr size=1> Maijun, if EQ needs to be revised 100%, wouldn't that mean it is operating at 0%? (Assuming you want the maximum gameplay, 100% being the maximum). This having been said, have you already quit EQ? If not, why are you posting things like that? If I played a game that operated at 0% gameplay, I wouldn't bother posting on the rogue boards, I'd play another game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And in response to the guy mentioning all the labels on the maps we get with our EQ boxes and the fact that they should be made into zones, there is no need. <br>
        These labels, i.e. Dragonscale Hills, are just like landmarks. In fact, I'm sure the majority of these locations are actually already IN zones, it's just that most people don't refer to the ocean in Odus as the Abysmal Sea merely because, sadly, most EQ players aren't roleplayers and tend to adapt to easily remembered sayings, like, the water in Odus, lol. But I agree with you, more zones is a great idea, though look at what's happening now: we are having to upgrade our computers just to play the new expansion. <br>
       New zones = more time = more patching = more problems = more money. We are recieving some new zones with SoL, but if Verant responded to all the requests I'm sure they get for new zones, the game would be almost too large, and the changed wouldn't occur immediately.   Not even the best programmers can crank out 20 new zones in a month. Surely the guys at Sony are already brainstorming a new expansion, and taking these suggestions to heart, as I bet they did with Sol, Velious, and RoK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=miladas>Miladas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 10:24:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should verant finally fix the old EQ?</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure that Stonebrunt was to be the last &quot;free&quot; zone in the old world.  As in, the last zone that they'd put in without you having to buy an expansion.<br>
<br>
I resent the fact that I play on Karana and never got to hunt in Cazic-Thule or SolB or any of the old dungeons (I started playing around the release of Kunark).  Now, I'm practically forced to hunt in OT and DL (just got out of OT now).  I even have a hell of a time finding a group in Velious - dungeon or outside zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaijun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maijun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 11:21:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should verant finally fix the old EQ?</span><hr size=1> Toklan, revised means to review, to look something over... and when I say &quot;revise 100%&quot;, I say it because I think EQ could be so much more better than it actually is.  And no...what I said has nothing to do w/ operating at 0%... nothing remotely close to it.<br>
<br>
I've been off eq for about 7 months and yes I still come here because A) I can and B) I was once an addict and I often enjoy checking up on the Rogue class and society as a whole.  <br>
<br>
Maybe I'm a little bitter... mostly because I belive SoL did nothing really for eq.  I see it as eye candy... much like AO.  Sure it added new items/zones/race/class, but they're are already 50+ vah shir, and many of the functioning zones of SoL have already been &quot;owned.&quot;  So, I believe instead of bringing out a new expansion, they should redo eq, like stated above, from the ground up... and I'm not just talking about eq's sad excuse for quests... I'm talking about the whole game.<br>
<br>
<br>
Straife Silently<br>
Disgruntled and Retired<br>
